<FIRST>r a AM-ActorSued     05-18 0251</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Actor Sued,0258</SECOND>
<HEAD>Atlantan Files Suit Against Rob Lowe for `Porn' Video</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Atlanta resident has accused actor Rob Lowe in
a civil lawsuit of making sexual videotapes with a minor female.
   The lawsuit contends the 25-year-old actor ``used his celebrity
status as an inducement to females to engage in sexual intercourse,
sodomy and multiple party sexual activity for his immediate sexual
gratification and for the purpose of making pornographic films of
these activities.''
   The lawsuit, filed Friday in Fulton County State Court, alleges
that Lowe seduced a minor into appearing in the tapes with him and
another person while he was in Atlanta for last summer's Democratic
National Convention.
   Lowe has starred in such movies as ``St. Elmo's Fire'' and
``About Last Night.''
   A copy of the lawsuit was obtained by television station WGNX in
Atlanta before it was sealed, at the request of Lowe's attorney,
within an hour of its filing Friday. The name of the plaintiff was
not available Thursday night.
   County District Attorney Lewis Slaton said he has a copy of the
videotape and is reviewing it to determine whether criminal charges
would be filed.
   The civil lawsuit asks for unspecified punitive damages for
emotional harm inflicted upon the female.
   An agent for Lowe said late Thursday that the actor and his
manager, Tim Wood, were out of the country Thursday and couldn't be
reached for comment by telephone.
   Lowe's attorney in Atlanta, Edgar Neely III, did not return
telephone calls Thursday night.
</TEXT>
