<FIRST>r a AM-WorkersBurned     05-18 0188</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Workers Burned,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>12 Track Workers Injured In Tunnel Explosion</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Caren 2nd is CQ</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A dozen workers installing track in a subway
tunnel were injured Wednesday, three of them seriously burned, when
a section of new rail touched the 600-volt electrified third rail,
the Transit Authority said.
   Two of the burned workers were in critical but stable condition,
and the third was in serious condition, said Kathy McGowan, a
spokeswoman for New York Hospital-Cornell Burn Center.
   The other nine workers were treated at two hospitals and
discharged.
   The workers were installing a 26-foot rail between two stations
in Brooklyn and had placed a protective rubber mat across the third
rail.
   Apparently ``the rail they were installing somehow slit the mat
and came in contact with the third rail,'' said Caren Gardner, a TA
spokeswoman. The mat was sent for testing to determine it was
slashed, she said.
   It is standard operating practice not to shut off electricity to
the third rail while crews are installing a single rail, Ms.
Gardner said.
   The Transit Authority will convene a board of inquiry on Friday.
</TEXT>
