<NOTE>Group Seeks to Probe Alleged Abuses of Child-Labor Laws</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A consumers group is starting a national
campaign to investigate alleged abuses of child-labor laws and to
pressure governments to improve enforcement of the standards.
   The National Consumers League also said Wednesday it would seek
to determine the impact of increased employment among teen-agers on
education and family and personal relationships.
