<TEXT>
   Anne Henderson-Pollard, convicted of
helping her husband pass intelligence secrets to Israel, has been
returned to the federal prison here.
   Henderson-Pollard, who is serving a five-year sentence for being
an accessory, was transferred Tuesday from the Federal Medical
Clinic in Rochester, Minn., prison officials said.
   She had been taken to Minnesota after she collapsed in January.
