<HEAD>Man Sentenced for Distributing Videotapes of Affair</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST DETROIT, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man convicted of misdemeanor
charges for distributing hundreds of videotapes that showed him
having sex with a married woman was placed on probation and warned
to stay away from her.
   Eric Sanderson, 45, of Troy, was sentenced Tuesday to 21 months'
probation, $6,300 in court costs and fines and 416 hours of
community service. He was ordered to stay at least 2,000 yards away
from his ex-lover's house and her husband's business.
   ``It will be straight to jail for you without passing `Go,'''
East Detroit Municipal Judge Benedict Segesta told Sanderson.
   Police said the woman told them she had an affair with Sanderson
in 1987-88. After she broke up with him, he distributed videotapes
he had made surreptitiously of them having sex, she said.
   He was convicted in February of assault and battery, telephone
harassment, reckless driving and littering, all misdemeanors.
