<SECOND>AM-BRF--Japan-Accident,0111</SECOND>
<HEAD>One Killed, Four Injured in Artillery Exercise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An accident during an artillery exercise killed one
soldier and injured four others Thursday, an official of the Ground
Self-Defense Force said.
   It was the first such accident since Japan began using the 155
self-propelled howitzers in 1975, said the official, who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
   The accident, which is under investigation, occurred at
Yausubetsu, one of five major exercise facilities in Hokkaido,
Japan's northernmost main island. More than 120 soldiers were
involved in the exercise, the official said.
   About one-third of Japan's 155,000 Ground Self-Defense Force
troops are stationed in Hokkaido, he said.
