<HEAD>Man Charged With Beating Children Allegedly Made Them Smoke Crack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man forced five children in his care
to smoke crack, held their heads under water and beat them with a
broom and stick, then claimed ``God told him to do it,'' police
said.
   Tony Carter, 36, was jailed on $35,000 bail on charges of
battery and possession of cocaine.
   The children, ages 4, 6, 7, 8 and 11, were in good condition at
Arkansas Children's Hospital, where traces of cocaine were found in
their blood, police said. The children will be placed in foster
care, police said.
