   A joint statement signed by several Gonaives radio reporters
protested ``the blind and brutal repression which has always
characterized the army in Gonaives in its dealings with an unarmed
population,'' Radio Soleil said.
   After the incident, soldiers shot repeatedly into the air to
keep residents inside, Radio Soleil said.
