Corp. withdrew its offer to acquire rival Avon Products Inc.
   The move came late Wednesday, just hours after Avon's board
rejected Amway's $39-a-share offer saying that uniting the nation's
two biggest companies in person-to-person sales would cause a
culture clash with disastrous consequences.
