<FIRST>r f PM-Eastern-Psychiatrists     05-18 0375</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Eastern-Psychiatrists,0388</SECOND>
<HEAD>Lorenzo Says He Has Psychiatrists Evaluating Union Literature</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: Note contents in last graf may offend some readers; Also moved
for Thursday AMs</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Eastern, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARCY GORDON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eastern Airlines boss Frank Lorenzo has accused
the carrier's striking unions of brainwashing members and has asked
psychiatrists to study the materials sent by strike leaders to the
rank and file.
   In a speech last Friday to students at Stanford University's
business school, Lorenzo, chairman of Eastern's parent Texas Air
Corp., said the psychiatrists met in Washington to examine the
union literature.
   Texas Air spokesman Art Kent said the company had no immediate
comment on Lorenzo's remarks. An account of Lorenzo's speech in
Palo Alto, Calif., was released by the business school.
   ``We have people here (in the unions) who have been totally,
completely brainwashed,'' said Lorenzo, as quoted by the Stanford
press release.
   ``We have, in fact, a meeting going on today in Washington,
D.C., by a bunch of psychiatrists and psychoanalysts who are going
through the propaganda materials that these people are being sent.
And this is brainwashing in the style of the '40s.
   ``What is being put into their heads gets them excited about
giving up their jobs and giving up their careers.''
   It was unclear from Lorenzo's remarks whether he had hired the
psychiatrists. It also was unclear how he intended to use their
analysis of the union materials.
   Dan Ashby, a spokesman in New York for the Eastern pilots union,
on Wednesday called Lorenzo's remarks ``a continuation of his
desperation tactics.''
   ``We would suggest that Mr. Lorenzo sit down with these people
(the psychiatrists) and find out what his own problems are,'' he
said. ``We're very sane people; we're very serious about what we're
doing.''
   Since March 4, pilots and flight attendants at Miami-based
Eastern have supported a strike by the airline's Machinists union.
Lorenzo put Eastern into Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection on March
9.
   Protestors threw eggs in Lorenzo's direction before he entered
the auditorium to make his one-hour speech, and called him
``Hitler'' and ``greedy bastard'' when he left, the business
school's news release said. It also said the 200 or so protestors
included pilots and machinists at Eastern.
</TEXT>
