<FIRST>r f PM-ConrailChief     05-18 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Conrail Chief,0169</SECOND>
<HEAD>Conrail Board Elects Hagen Chief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   James A. Hagen, chosen last month to head
Conrail, was elected as chairman, president and chief executive
officer of the Philadelphia-based freight railroad.
   Hagen, 57, former president and chief executive officer of CSX
Distribution Services Group, also was elected a director at a board
meeting after Conrail's annual shareholders meeting Wednesday.
   He succeeds veteran railroader Stanley E.G. Hillman, who took
over as interim chief after the death Feb. 12 of Richard D. Sanborn.
   Conrail's board announced April 4 it had chosen Hagen to fill
the position effective Thursday. He officially joined Conrail April
17.
   Before joining CSX, Hagen was Conrail's senior vice president
for marketing and sales from February 1977 to April 1985.
   He formerly worked with Southern Railway, the Missouri Pacific
Railroad and two federal rail agencies, including the United States
Railway Association, which was formed to create Conrail from the
Penn Central and five other bankrupt Northeast railroads.
</TEXT>
