<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
251,862 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
247,776, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 262,781 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
